thread.title: Texans' Arian Foster likely out for rest of season
thread.title_full: Texans' Arian Foster likely out for rest of season

author: JUSTIN TASCH
title: Texans' Arian Foster likely out for rest of season
text:
Share this URL Joel Auerbach/AP Texans running back Arian Foster (l.) grabs a touchdown pass Sunday but is likely lost for the season. 
A long day for the Texans ended in one of the worst ways possible. 
Arian Foster, playing in garbage time in the fourth quarter after the Dolphins built up a 41-point lead, was carted off with what the Texans called an Achilles’ injury. ESPN reported that doctors believe Foster’s Achilles’ is torn, which would end his season.

Foster’s injury was of the non-contact variety as he stumbled running off the snap as he came out of motion. 
The running back missed most of training camp and the first three games of the season because of a groin tear. Related Stories
